defs.docs:
Bincode is a crate for encoding and decoding using a tiny binary
 serialization strategy.  Using it, you can easily go from having
 an object in memory, quickly serialize it to bytes, and then
 deserialize it back just as fast!

defs.name: Config
defs.docs:
A configuration builder whose options Bincode will use
 while serializing and deserializing.

defs.name: no_limit
defs.docs:
Sets the byte limit to be unlimited.
 This is the default.

defs.name: limit
defs.docs: Sets the byte limit to `limit`.

defs.name: little_endian
defs.docs:
Sets the endianness to little-endian
 This is the default.

defs.name: big_endian
defs.docs: Sets the endianness to big-endian

defs.name: native_endian
defs.docs: Sets the endianness to the the machine-native endianness

defs.name: serialize
defs.docs: Serializes a serializable object into a `Vec` of bytes using this configuration

defs.name: serialized_size
defs.docs: Returns the size that an object would be if serialized using Bincode with this configuration

Deserializes an object from a custom `BincodeRead`er using the default configuration.

defs.docs: The result of a serialization or deserialization operation.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: An error that can be produced during (de)serializing.

defs.name: Io
defs.docs:
If the error stems from the reader/writer that is being used
 during (de)serialization, that error will be stored and returned here.

defs.name: InvalidUtf8Encoding
defs.docs: Returned if the deserializer attempts to deserialize a string that is not valid utf8

defs.name: InvalidBoolEncoding
defs.docs:
Returned if the deserializer attempts to deserialize a bool that was
 not encoded as either a 1 or a 0

defs.name: InvalidCharEncoding
defs.docs: Returned if the deserializer attempts to deserialize a char that is not in the correct format.

defs.name: InvalidTagEncoding
defs.docs:
Returned if the deserializer attempts to deserialize the tag of an enum that is
 not in the expected ranges

defs.name: DeserializeAnyNotSupported
defs.docs:
Serde has a deserialize_any method that lets the format hint to the
 object which route to take in deserializing.

defs.name: SizeLimit
defs.docs:
If (de)serializing a message takes more than the provided size limit, this
 error is returned.

defs.name: SequenceMustHaveLength
defs.docs: Bincode can not encode sequences of unknown length (like iterators).

defs.name: Custom
defs.docs: A custom error message from Serde.
